[p 
	(listlanguages|istranslation=true)
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[h2 id=WhatisFDS? 
	" What is FDS?
	$LF
]h2
[p 
	"FDS stands for Famicom Disk System.
	[br 
	]br
	$LF
	"It's a special Famicom-like (Famicom is the Japanese
	$LF
	"name of Nintendo Entertainment System) console where
	$LF
	"games are loaded from diskettes.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"FDS images are different from NES images in that they
	$LF
	"are usually named 
	[tt 
		".fds
	]tt
	", not 
	[tt 
		".nes
	]tt
	",
	$LF
	"and that you also need a disk system BIOS image
	$LF
	"(usually named as 
	[tt 
		"disksys.rom
	]tt
	" for emulators).
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"This site does not distribute FDS images or 
	[tt 
		"disksys.rom
	]tt
	".
	$LF
]p
[h3 id=PlayingFDSfilesinFCEUX 
	" Playing FDS files in FCEUX
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"A special ROM named 
	[tt 
		"disksys.rom
	]tt
	" is required to play FDS files (files ending in 
	[tt 
		".fds
	]tt
	"). It should be about 8K in size. If it is not named 
	[tt 
		"disksys.rom
	]tt
	", it is the wrong file. Do not rename any files. Place 
	[tt 
		"disksys.rom
	]tt
	" in your FCEU folder. Then run the FDS file in FCEUX.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Do not use so-called "FDS hacks". They do not work.
]p
